    • Constructor Detail

      • Lex

        public Lex(IntVar[][] x)
        It creates a lexicographical order for vectors x[i], i.e. forall i, exists j : x[i][k] = x[i+1][k] for k < j and x[i][k] <= x[i+1][k] for k >= j vectors x[i] does not need to be of the same size. boolea lt defines if we require Lex_{<} (lt = false) or Lex_{=<} (lt = true)
        Parameters:
        x - vector of vectors which assignment is constrained by Lex constraint.
